5
A Star Point Pattern (48)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0\deflang1033\deflangfe1042{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par \b Black to Play.\b0
\par In the knight's approach/two-space high pincer pattern, the most active move for white to play is a double-approach.
\par
\par Black has many options in responding, and the variantion can be difficult. Let's study the basic shapes.
\par }
