W[qn]
Diagram 1 (From the Other Direction)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par The most frequently used countermeasure for black to employ is  the attachment of 1. In this case, attaching to the stone which black is not focussed on attacking.
\par
\par In this way, black gets momentum in preparation for attacking  the white \'a1\'e2 stone.
\par }
