B[pn]
Diagram 2 (Hane After the Attachment)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White naturally hanes at 1. There is a proverb which states, "Hane when your opponent attaches". Next, black extends with 2.
\par
\par The difficulties appear when white invades the corner at the 3-3 point.
\par
\par How should black respond to this?
\par }
