Diagram 3 (Black, Dissatisfied)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par In a real game, black's block at 1, is commonly seen. In this case, white can be satisfied to simply cross under with 2.
\par
\par Up to 8, white's the profit white gains is large.
\par
\par On the other hand, black is dissatisfied as black's \'a1\'e3 stone is in an awkward place.
\par
\par Unless playing a handicap game, you should not play like this.
\par }
