Diagram 4 (A Typical Bad Move)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Instead of wedging in between white's stones and then connecting, it is a typical bad move for black to turn at 1.
\par
\par Now, white will immediately play a wedge with 2 and connect at 4.
\par
\par Black also connects with 5 but it is bad shape. White's profit is even greater than in the previous diagram. Black is in an unfavorable position.
\par }
